Members of an Oxford University drinking society were branded ‘repugnant and sexist’ yesterday for organising a pub crawl in which girls dressed as foxes have to ‘evade mauling’.

The Black Cygnets Society at St Hugh’s College sent invitations to the female first-year students its members consider to be the most attractive.

The ‘Fox Hunt’ event involves male students, or ‘Huntsmen’, dressed in red jackets chasing the women ‘Foxes’ dressed in short skirts and fox ears.

