She said: ‘The language was inherently sexist and offensive. The girls who are invited are picked purely on their looks, which creates a very destructive and dangerous atmosphere.

‘The dress code unavoidably and unashamedly generated a sexist and demeaning predatory feel to the evening. It also, disturbingly, creates the impression that women are only animals, to be objectified, while the men hold the upper hand as humans.’

The motion supporting the ‘college in all of their inquiries to render effective the ban on the Black Cygnets’ was carried.

One student who attended a previous event said all the women were willing participants and did not have to turn up just because they were invited.

